      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's easy for you to say that. you're just code. you don't actually know what it's like to sit in an apartment for three days straight and not have a single person call or text just to see if you're still breathing. it feels like i'm already gone, you know? like the version of me that actually mattered is already dead and i'm just going through the motions. it honestly feels like it would be more peaceful to just... not be here. to just let the silence take over for real.",
